text:
Hi I was sent here by HubSpot help as they didnt seem to have any information. I have various dev accounts to test my app integration. Some are for manual tests and others are for integration tests which i dont want to mess about with. I recently got an email for all of my dev accounts saying:

"Your HubSpot plan has changed and doesn't allow primary Email, Knowledge base HubSpot (system) domains, so you'll need to head to Domains & URLs within 89 days to remove them. Or, if you do nothing, on Apr 19, 2023 we'll automatically remove them."

problem is that I cant really understand what it wants me to do as I do not have any domains registered on these accounts...
I might just be misunderstanding what it wants me to do so please clarify if you have any ideas.

Thanks in advance - also apologies if this isnt the right place to be posting this.
Hi <@U03AKL6Q1B2> Thanks for those docs. They are a massive help! Cheers!
